## ğŸ§  Supabase Client Setup (READ THIS OR SUFFER)

This app uses **a singleton Supabase client** stored in `src/lib/supabaseClient.ts`.

### Why this matters:
- Supabaseâ€™s GoTrueClient **throws warnings** (and can behave weirdly) if multiple instances are created in the same browser context.
- Hot module reloading during dev will often trigger this unless we **guard with a global singleton**.
- Some legacy files (like `src/integrations/supabase/client.ts`) **must not** create their own `createClient(...)` instances.

### âœ… How It Works
We use a global `globalThis.__supabase` instance to ensure Supabase is only initialized once â€” even across HMR or duplicate imports.

```ts
// src/lib/supabaseClient.ts
if (!globalThis.__supabase) {
  globalThis.__supabase = createClient(...);
}
export const supabase = globalThis.__supabase;
```

### ğŸš« Don't Do This
- âŒ Donâ€™t call `createClient(...)` in other files
- âŒ Donâ€™t use hardcoded URLs or keys
- âŒ Donâ€™t import from `@supabase/supabase-js` directly outside of `supabaseClient.ts`

### âœ… Do This Instead
- âœ… Always `import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabaseClient'`
- âœ… Restart your dev server after `.env` changes
- âœ… Clear LocalStorage/SessionStorage if auth starts acting weird

---

This pattern is dev-safe, prod-safe, and wonâ€™t trigger the "Multiple GoTrueClient instances detected" warning ever again.
